    "title": "Mid-Level Fleet Manager at AirAsia Cargo India",
    "description": "Join the AirAsia Cargo India family as a Fleet Manager in Chandigarh. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout AirAsia Cargo India:\nAirAsia Cargo India is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage reverse logistics and return merchandise authorization\n• Coordinate with warehousing teams for inbound and outbound operations\n• Implement cost-saving initiatives in transportation and warehousing\n• Coordinate with customer service teams to resolve delivery issues\n• Track shipments in real-time and resolve delivery exceptions\n• Manage relationships with third-party logistics providers\n• Implement warehouse management systems (WMS) and track KPIs\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Cold Chain Logistics\n• Proficiency in Customs Clearance\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in Fleet Management\n• Proficiency in INCOTERMS\n• Proficiency in Freight Forwarding\n• Proficiency in SAP SCM\n• Proficiency in WMS\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Referral bonus program\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Chandigarh, Punjab, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with AirAsia Cargo India!",
